detail.title: Upgrade to v1.4.0
detail.description:
This proposal if voted will upgrade the chain to v1.4.0
## Upgrade Features
This release contains a number of chain updates including:
- ICA controller
- Intertx module
- Token burn message
- Wasm state sync
- Upgrade handler
## Release
https://github.com/TERITORI/teritori-chain/releases/tag/v1.4.0
## Details of Upgrade Time
The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 3699425, anticipated to be on June 7th 2023 at 14:00 UTC.
Because blocks can occur at irregular intervals, please keep an eye on the chain for a precise upgrade time.

detail.title: TORI buy back
detail.description:
## TORI buy back

### Description

As part of TORI 2.0 proposals, use 100% of the inApp generated fees that are not TORI but other IBC denoms (ATOM and more coming later) from:

- NFT launchpad (5% to 10% of each mint).
- NFT marketplace (2% of each sale).
- The R!ot (TORI) P2E breeding (XYZ ATOM per breeding).

And use 100% of them for TORI buy back so the bought back TORI are split as the following:

Redistribute 40% of them in the Usage Incentive pool.
Burn 60% of them.

### Voting

By voting “Yes” you believe this the way

By voting “No” you believe this is not the way

detail.title: Increase Minimum Deposit for Governance Proposals
detail.description:
### Summary 

We propose to increase minimum deposit for proposals to 20000 TORI. 

### Description 

The current deposit for the offer is 500 TORI, which is very low compared to other Cosmos chains. For this reason, spam proposals are sent. To prevent this, we recommend increasing the deposit amount to 20000 TORI. 

### Voting 

By voting 'Yes' you agree to raise the minimum deposit for governance proposals to 20000 TORI.

By voting 'No' you do not agree to raise the minimum deposit for governance proposals to 20000 TORI.

detail.title: Min deposit param change
detail.description: Several spam spam proposals have been submitted in the past days (#10 ,#11, #12, #13, #14, #15, #16, #17) and TORI price currently allows to spam the chain with fake proposals very cheapy. We have decided to propose the community to increase the min amount of TORI that should be deposited for a governance proposal from 500 TORI to 4000 TORI (~100$ considering a TORI price of 0.03$). This should make it less likely for bad actors to create scam or spam proposals in the future, preserving the real meaning of on-chain governance.

detail.title: Community Pool Spend Proposal for Junoswap Liquidity incentives
detail.description:
This proposal requests 750000 tori to be allocated to JUNO/TORI pool for 90days on junoswap.

Requesting to incentivize another pool on a different chain to give more exposure to the Teritori chain.

If the proposal passes the funds will be allocated to the multisig wallet controlled by the Teritori core team. which will then deploy the incentives to the JUNO/TORI pool.

Address:tori1f9g9evflknke650mx5ut3zlzmxtl5wga9fqxal.

## Voting

By voting YES on this proposal, you agree to allocate 750000 tori to JUNO/TORI pool for 90days as incentives.
By voting NO on this proposal, you disagree that the Pool should be incentivised.
By voting NO WITH VETO, you disagree with incentivising the pool, and additionally wish to see depositors penalized.
By voting ABSTAIN, you decline to give an opinion on the incentivising the pool.

This proposal, if passed would distribute the requested LP amount to the core development multi-sig account, which will deploy the funds to the above mentioned pools on 14/10/2022.
The prop #1 incentive program will last for 120 days.

OSMO/TORI = 16666.6 TORI/day

The funds will be managed by a Multisig Core Team wallet at the address below:

Address:
tori1f9g9evflknke650mx5ut3zlzmxtl5wga9fqxal

Important:
These incentives will go live on 14/10/2022.
Retroactive rewards will not go into effect for this proposal.
